    explanation: "**Geriatric surgical / oncologic care** — individualization paramount given heterogeneity of elderly. **Heterogeneity**: chronologic age ≠ biological age. Many 80-yr-olds robust, some 60-yr-olds frail. **Comprehensive Geriatric Assessment (CGA)** — multidimensional; predicts outcomes better than chronological age alone. **Tools**: - Frailty: Fried, Clinical Frailty Scale (CFS — Rockwood), Modified Frailty Index, Edmonton Frail - Cognition: MMSE, MoCA, Mini-Cog, delirium (CAM) - Function: ADL/IADL, gait speed (slow < 0.8 m/s independent risk), grip strength - Comorbidity: Charlson, CIRS-G - Polypharmacy: Beers, STOPP/START - Cancer-specific: G8, CARG (chemo toxicity), CRASH score **Geriatric oncology principles**: - Tumor biology + behavior - Patient's functional + cognitive reserve - Life expectancy estimation (ePrognosis tools — Lee, Schonberg) - 'Lag time to benefit' — does intervention's benefit timeline align with patient's expected longevity? - Treatment intensity individualization (full, modified, supportive) - Geriatric assessment improves treatment outcomes + patient satisfaction (Mohile et al evidence) **Polypharmacy + deprescribing**: - Beers Criteria — potentially inappropriate medications (PIM) for elderly - STOPP/START — Screening Tool of Older Person's Prescriptions + Screening Tool to Alert to Right Treatment - Common deprescribing targets: anticholinergics, BZD, opioids, NSAIDs, sliding scale insulin alone, multiple antihypertensives, statin in limited life expectancy + frailty - Reduces falls, cognitive impairment, drug interactions, costs **Delirium prevention** — HELP (Hospital Elder Life Program), ABCDEF bundle, NICE delirium guidelines: orientation, mobilization, hydration, vision/hearing aids, sleep hygiene, minimize anticholinergic + benzodiazepine, family presence, avoid restraints + Foley + restrictive environment. **Goals of care + advance care planning**: ongoing conversations; documented; portable (POLST/MOLST); honor patient's values. **Function-focused care**: primary aim — maintain/restore function vs disease cure alone. PT, OT, rehab, home safety, assistive devices, fall prevention (multifactorial intervention works). **Models of care**: - ACE (Acute Care for Elders) units — inpatient geriatric model improves outcomes - PACE (Programs of All-Inclusive Care for Elderly) — community-based - Geriatric consult services - Co-management (orthogeriatrics, geriatric trauma) - ACS Geriatric Surgery Verification Program (since 2019) — institutional standards.",
